Most likely your page's `BindingContext` is never set. The `{Binding}` markup needs a source object. In your code-behind, wire it up:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

Also ensure your ViewModel raises change notifications:

```csharp
public class MyViewModel : INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    public event PropertyChangedEventHandler PropertyChanged;

    private string _title;
    public string Title
    {
        get => _title;
        set { _title = value; PropertyChanged?.Invoke(this, new(nameof(Title))); }
    }
}
```

**TL;DR** — two things to check:
1. **`BindingContext` not set** — most common cause of blank labels.
2. **No `INotifyPropertyChanged`** — if properties are set *after* construction, the UI won't update without it.
